01:23:25,583 --> 01:23:29,750
As it happens, I own a small
trinket stand across the way.

1055
01:23:32,292 --> 01:23:35,749
Well, it's uh... it's no use.

1056
01:23:35,750 --> 01:23:38,541
Well, you never know.

1057
01:23:38,542 --> 01:23:40,208
I got a lot of stuff.

1058
01:23:40,500 --> 01:23:41,542
Well, no, no, no, no.

1059
01:23:44,042 --> 01:23:46,666
It's my monkey.
I've looked everywhere.

1060
01:23:46,667 --> 01:23:48,916
I just, I can't find it.

1061
01:23:48,917 --> 01:23:51,166
You lost a monkey?

1062
01:23:51,167 --> 01:23:53,291
What, a chimpanzee
from your show?

1063
01:23:53,292 --> 01:23:56,416
No. A toy monkey.

1064
01:23:56,417 --> 01:23:58,249
A toy monkey?

1065
01:23:58,250 --> 01:23:59,416
You mean, the kind with cymbals?

1066
01:23:59,417 --> 01:24:01,707
You've seen it?

1067
01:24:01,708 --> 01:24:02,832
That's the damnedest thing.

1068
01:24:02,833 --> 01:24:05,167
This morning, some bum walks up
and says for a dollar,

1069
01:24:06,042 --> 01:24:09,582
he'll give me this toy monkey.

1070
01:24:09,583 --> 01:24:10,707
You know, like the one
you're looking for.

1071
01:24:10,708 --> 01:24:13,041
It was in good condition,
so I said okay.

1072
01:24:13,042 --> 01:24:15,832
You've got it?

1073
01:24:15,833 --> 01:24:17,166
You're not going to believe
this, not about an hour ago,

1074
01:24:17,167 --> 01:24:19,332
an old lady pulls up in a car
and offers me 20 bucks for it.

1075
01:24:19,333 --> 01:24:23,249
Twenty bucks!
I couldn't believe it.

1076
01:24:23,250 --> 01:24:25,332
So, you sold it to her?

1077
01:24:25,333 --> 01:24:27,291
Damn right. I would've
given her half my cart

1078
01:24:27,292 --> 01:24:29,707
for 20 bucks.

1079
01:24:29,708 --> 01:24:32,291
Well, did you get her name

1080
01:24:32,292 --> 01:24:34,832
or where she lives?
Anything?

1081
01:24:34,833 --> 01:24:36,708
Well actually, yeah.

1082
01:24:37,833 --> 01:24:40,250
Her name's Marie Andrews.

1083
01:24:42,667 --> 01:24:46,041
312 Maple Drive.

1084
01:24:46,042 --> 01:24:49,166
Granted I don't usually
accept checks,

1085
01:24:49,167 --> 01:24:51,000
but she looked
respectful enough.

1086
01:25:06,208 --> 01:25:09,375
( CHATTERING )

1087
01:25:17,333 --> 01:25:21,207
Oh, thank you, darling, so much!

1088
01:25:21,208 --> 01:25:22,999
I'll give you a call.

1089
01:25:23,000 --> 01:25:24,332
FEMALE DRIVER:
Oh, please do!

1090
01:25:24,333 --> 01:25:25,333
Ok darling, alright.

1091
01:25:25,333 --> 01:25:26,333
DRIVER: Bye-bye!

1092
01:25:26,667 --> 01:25:27,667
Mary!

1093
01:25:29,875 --> 01:25:30,875
Oh, my I've missed you!

1094
01:25:30,876 --> 01:25:33,332
Welcome home!

1095
01:25:33,333 --> 01:25:34,292
Oh, thank you so much!

1096
01:25:34,293 --> 01:25:35,791
Why didn't you call me?

1097
01:25:35,792 --> 01:25:38,291
Oh well, Sarah...
I would have come to get you. (
GROANS ) Sand in here?

1098
01:25:38,292 --> 01:25:40,291
Sarah was at the airport

1099
01:25:40,292 --> 01:25:41,749
which worked out
just wonderfully.

1100
01:25:41,750 --> 01:25:43,207
You have the best luck, I swear.

1101
01:25:43,208 --> 01:25:45,249
Oh, tell me, how are you, Pete?

1102
01:25:45,250 --> 01:25:46,957
Fine.
Oh, good.

1103
01:25:46,958 --> 01:25:48,332
And do you have any new
old cars to tell me about?

1104
01:25:48,333 --> 01:25:50,666
Well, I sold the old Chevy,

1105
01:25:50,667 --> 01:25:51,667
and I'm gonna start
on the old Buick next.

1106
01:25:51,668 --> 01:25:53,041
Oh, great.
How is everything?

1107
01:25:53,042 --> 01:25:55,166
Fine, except that son
of yours is a lousy cook.

1108
01:25:55,167 --> 01:25:57,666
Oh! ( LAUGHS )

1109
01:25:57,667 --> 01:25:59,291
And how was Hawaii?

1110
01:25:59,292 --> 01:26:00,332
Wonderful!

1111
01:26:00,333 --> 01:26:01,333
( LAUGHING )

1112
01:26:03,500 --> 01:26:05,332
Well, Pete, I might just
tell him you know.

1113
01:26:05,333 --> 01:26:07,582
Grandma!

1114
01:26:07,583 --> 01:26:09,291
Oh, Michael!

1115
01:26:09,292 --> 01:26:11,291
How are you, darling?

1116
01:26:11,292 --> 01:26:12,292
Oh damn,
wouldn't you know it, Mary,

1117
01:26:12,293 --> 01:26:13,999
there's my phone.
I'll talk to you later.

1118
01:26:14,000 --> 01:26:15,416
All right, Pete.
Thank you so much!

1119
01:26:15,417 --> 01:26:16,957
PETE: Welcome home.
Oh, thank you!

1120
01:26:16,958 --> 01:26:18,666
Michael, how are you?

1121
01:26:18,667 --> 01:26:20,416
Fine. Is that for me?

1122
01:26:20,417 --> 01:26:21,999
DAVID: Is that you, Mom?
Yes!

1123
01:26:22,000 --> 01:26:24,082
How was your birthday?

1124
01:26:24,083 --> 01:26:25,042
Did you have a party?

1125
01:26:25,043 --> 01:26:26,332
Yeah. Can I open
my present now?

1126
01:26:26,333 --> 01:26:28,332
Well, take it over to the table

1127
01:26:28,333 --> 01:26:29,999
and wait till Dad comes.
Okay?

1128
01:26:30,000 --> 01:26:32,167
Okay.

1129
01:26:33,583 --> 01:26:37,332
DAVID: Mom!
MARY: Hi!

1130
01:26:37,333 --> 01:26:38,999
Oh David!
What has happened to you?

1131
01:26:39,000 --> 01:26:41,291
Don't even ask, Mom.

1132
01:26:41,292 --> 01:26:42,499
Have you been in
an accident or something?

1133
01:26:42,500 --> 01:26:44,291
Look, you wouldn't believe me
if I told you.

1134
01:26:44,292 --> 01:26:45,707
Can I open my present now?

1135
01:26:45,708 --> 01:26:47,166
Please, Grandma!
Please?

1136
01:26:47,167 --> 01:26:48,291
Yes, dear, you may.

1137
01:26:48,292 --> 01:26:49,292
David, are you sure
you're feeling all right?

1138
01:26:49,293 --> 01:26:50,916
I'm sure, Mom, just fine.
I'm fine.

1139
01:26:50,917 --> 01:26:53,291
Hey, did you see how well
I took care of your plants?

1140
01:26:53,292 --> 01:26:55,166
Oh, they're beautiful!

1141
01:26:55,167 --> 01:26:56,332
I can't believe
how much they've grown!

1142
01:26:56,333 --> 01:26:57,791
( LAUGHS )

1143
01:26:57,792 --> 01:26:59,332
Dad, look!

1144
01:26:59,333 --> 01:27:00,333
Isn't it, darling?

1145
01:27:03,708 --> 01:27:06,999
Michael, go outside!

1146
01:27:07,000 --> 01:27:09,332
David?

1147
01:27:09,333 --> 01:27:10,167
Don't ask questions, Mom.

1148
01:27:10,168 --> 01:27:11,332
( BOTH TALKING
OVER EACH OTHER )

1149
01:27:11,333 --> 01:27:12,916
David, David!

1150
01:27:12,917 --> 01:27:15,291
Mom!

1151
01:27:15,292 --> 01:27:16,292
Dad! Dad!

1152
01:27:18,500 --> 01:27:19,500
Dad!

1153
01:27:21,708 --> 01:27:24,416
DAVID: Open it!
MICHAEL: I can't!
David!

1154
01:27:24,417 --> 01:27:25,499
Get out of the way, Michael!

1155
01:27:25,500 --> 01:27:26,750
MICHAEL: Dad!

1156
01:27:28,250 --> 01:27:31,332
DAVID:
Run faster! Go!

1157
01:27:31,333 --> 01:27:33,291
Get in the car!

1158
01:27:33,292 --> 01:27:34,541
Mom, there's no time
to explain now.

1159
01:27:34,542 --> 01:27:35,999
Just get into the car!

1160
01:27:36,000 --> 01:27:37,000
Michael, get in...

1161
01:27:42,333 --> 01:27:45,750
Oh! You found it.

1162
01:27:47,417 --> 01:27:48,737
Sweetheart,
you can come home now.

1163
01:27:51,292 --> 01:27:53,833
GRANDPA: And so with the monkey
back in Merlin's possession,

1164
01:27:55,292 --> 01:27:58,708
Merlin could return home
with renewed hope.

1165
01:27:59,292 --> 01:28:03,332
Of course
he'd still have to decide

1166
01:28:03,333 --> 01:28:05,332
what to do with the monkey

1167
01:28:05,333 --> 01:28:07,253
to ensure nothing like this
ever happened again.

1168
01:28:07,375 --> 01:28:11,333
MERLIN:
I'll deal with you later.

1169
01:28:12,042 --> 01:28:13,167
But for now,

1170
01:28:15,333 --> 01:28:16,749
content that everything
was back to normal,

1171
01:28:16,750 --> 01:28:19,333
Merlin could re-open his shop
and continue his quest

1172
01:28:20,000 --> 01:28:23,875
to inspire the hopes
and dreams of all those

1173
01:28:24,458 --> 01:28:28,292
whose lives would soon
touch his own.

1174
01:28:47,542 --> 01:28:50,999
Goodnight, boy.

1175
01:28:51,000 --> 01:28:53,000
My goodness, you've grown big.

1176
01:28:53,667 --> 01:28:57,042
There you are.

1177
01:29:23,833 --> 01:29:27,292
( MUSIC PLAYING )

